## 1. GitOps Configuration Management

### Foundational Theory

GitOps was coined by Alexis Richardson (Weaveworks CEO) in 2017. The OpenGitOps specification (v1.0) codifies four non-negotiable principles:

| Principle | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Declarative** | Desired state expressed as data (YAML, TOML), never imperative commands |
| **Versioned and Immutable** | Git history is canonical; every state is addressed by commit SHA |
| **Pulled Automatically** | Agents inside the managed system fetch config from Git (not pushed from CI) |
| **Continuously Reconciled** | Agents constantly compare actual vs desired state and converge them |

The security model is inverted relative to push-based CI/CD: the live system never needs write credentials to its own config store. The reconciler needs only read access to Git and write access to the managed environment.

### ArgoCD Application CRD Pattern

ArgoCD (CNCF graduated, 2023) uses Kubernetes CRDs as its declaration surface. The `Application` CRD is the core pattern:

```yaml
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: Application
metadata:
  name: agent-fleet-prod
  namespace: argocd
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/version: "1.4.2"
spec:
  project: default
  source:
    repoURL: https://github.com/org/agent-configs
    targetRevision: main           # branch, tag, or commit SHA
    path: environments/production
  destination:
    server: https://kubernetes.default.svc
    namespace: agent-runtime
  syncPolicy:
    automated:
      enabled: true
      prune: true         # delete resources removed from Git
      selfHeal: true      # undo manual changes within ~3 minutes
      allowEmpty: false   # refuse to delete everything (safety rail)
    syncOptions:
      - CreateNamespace=true
      - PruneLast=true          # delete stale resources after new ones are Ready
      - Replace=false           # use kubectl apply, not replace
    retry:
      limit: 5
      backoff:
        duration: "5s"
        factor: 2
        maxDuration: "3m"
  revisionHistoryLimit: 10     # retain 10 past states for rollback
  ignoreDifferences:           # exclude ephemeral fields from drift detection
    - group: apps
      kind: Deployment
      jsonPointers:
        - /spec/replicas       # allow HPA to manage replica count
```

**Drift detection**: ArgoCD polls every 3 minutes (configurable via `timeout.reconciliation`). When `selfHeal: true`, any out-of-tree mutation (e.g., `kubectl edit`) is overwritten within the next reconciliation cycle.

**Rollback**: `argocd app rollback <app> <revision>` restores any prior state by commit SHA. The history window is controlled by `revisionHistoryLimit`.

### Flux CD GitRepository + Kustomization Pattern

Flux v2 (CNCF incubating) separates source management from reconciliation into distinct CRDs:

```yaml
# Source: defines WHERE to pull config from
apiVersion: source.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v1
kind: GitRepository
metadata:
  name: agent-configs
  namespace: flux-system
spec:
  interval: 1m           # poll frequency; minimum 60s
  url: https://github.com/org/agent-configs
  ref:
    branch: main
  secretRef:
    name: github-creds
  ignore: |              # gitignore-style exclusions
    *.md
    docs/
```

```yaml
# Reconciler: defines WHAT to apply and HOW
apiVersion: kustomize.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v1
kind: Kustomization
metadata:
  name: agent-fleet
  namespace: flux-system
spec:
  interval: 60m0s        # full reconciliation frequency
  retryInterval: 2m0s    # frequency on failure
  timeout: 3m0s          # per-operation timeout
  prune: true            # garbage-collect removed resources
  wait: true             # block until all resources reach Ready
  path: "./environments/production"
  sourceRef:
    kind: GitRepository
    name: agent-configs
  dependsOn:
    - name: cert-manager  # declare ordering dependencies
  healthChecks:
    - apiVersion: apps/v1
      kind: Deployment
      name: agent-dispatcher
  postBuild:
    substitute:
      AGENT_POOL_SIZE: "12"
      LOG_LEVEL: "info"
    substituteFrom:
      - kind: ConfigMap
        name: agent-runtime-vars
  decryption:
    provider: sops        # decrypt secrets at apply time
    secretRef:
      name: sops-age-key
```

